<Class name="CM_Bank" id="8ed662da-b8c4-4a41-97a6-fb3a56774a64">
    <superclass name="CM_FinancialObject"/>
    <persistentAllowed/>
    <sharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassPersistentAllowed/>
    <subclassSharedTransientAllowed/>
    <subclassTransientAllowed/>
    <transientAllowed/>
    <access>protected</access>
    <text>
Rename to CM_Company when Jade V6 is out

When change for full multi-terminal will also need to
investigating sub-classes and renaming some properties.

Currently it is only the Root company that has some of
the attributes (ie. debtorNodes/debtors).  It would be
better if these were moved to make this more obvious.

&lt;Documentation&gt;
&lt;NiceName&gt;Company&lt;/NiceName&gt;
&lt;Description&gt;
This is a Company.  Typically only one but if the system has mult-company enabled there may be more than one.
&lt;/Description&gt;
&lt;/Documentation&gt;</text>
